1. Chosen Development Model
Development Model: Agile
The Agile development model is chosen for the Sports Facility Booking System because it provides flexibility, adaptability, and continuous improvement throughout the development process. Agile allows the team to work in small iterations (sprints), where features can be developed, tested, and improved incrementally.
2. User Requirements
a. Stakeholders (WHO is involved)
1. Citizens (End Users)
Citizens are the primary users of the system. They use the platform to browse facilities, check availability, and make bookings. Their main interest is to have a simple, fast, and reliable booking experience.
2. Administrators
Administrators manage the system. They are responsible for managing facilities, schedules, users, and reports. Their goal is to ensure efficient operation and proper organization of the system.
3. Facility Staff
Facility staff assist in daily operations. They verify bookings, monitor schedules, and help users if needed. Their interest is to ensure that bookings are valid and facilities are used correctly.
4. Development Team
The development team (front-end, back-end, UI/UX designers) is responsible for building and maintaining the system. Their goal is to deliver a functional, secure, and user-friendly application.

b. User Stories (WHAT they need and WHY)
For Citizens
As a user, I want to register an account so that I can access the system and make bookings.
As a user, I want to log in securely so that my personal data is protected.
As a user, I want to view available sports facilities so that I can choose where to play.
As a user, I want to check real-time availability so that I can avoid booking conflicts.
As a user, I want to book a facility so that I can reserve a time slot easily.
As a user, I want to modify my booking so that I can adjust my schedule if needed.
As a user, I want to cancel a booking so that I can free the slot if my plans change.
As a user, I want to receive notifications and reminders so that I do not forget my bookings.
As a user, I want to view my booking history so that I can track my past and upcoming reservations. 
For Administrators
As an admin, I want to add and manage facilities so that the system remains updated.
As an admin, I want to manage users so that access and permissions are controlled.
As an admin, I want to view reports and usage statistics so that I can monitor system performance.
For Facility Staff
As staff, I want to verify bookings so that only valid users can use the facilities.
As staff, I want to view daily schedules so that I can manage facility usage efficiently.
